{"key":"processedPost-16948922","value":{"id":16948922,"first":16948231,"last":16967542,"when":1349150280,"utime":"10/02/12 06:58 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><strong>vagblast said:</strong><br />Peat/verm mix is always beter than just coir if that's what your asking. Coir is too nutritive and will get contams a lot easyer than peat/ verm</blockquote><br />This is incorrect.&nbsp; In fact it's the opposite.&nbsp; Coir is pretty contaminant resistant, while peat/verm casings are less forgiving, especially if not properly limed.<br />For the record to the original poster, if you're fruiting from straight grains without a bulk substrate, a casing layer is required.&nbsp; If you spawn the grains to a bulk substrate such as manure or coir, a casing layer is not required.<br />RR","title":"Re: casing ?"}}